          • [ - ] Champion - member since 11-Aug-17

            @neumi17 Aguero got 9.95 on the breakdown, Sterling 10.0 (meaning he would have most likely accumulated above 10.0 in individual points). Sterling won Aguero's penalty. 2 goals for Sterling, won the penalty Aguero converted vs 2 goals for Aguero plus a pen Sterling won. Sterling got the opening goal too and only had 2 shots. Sterling played as a wing forward vs the centre forward, resulting in less chances for him (2 shots vs 6 shots for Aguero). Sterling also had 2 key passes, 1 tackle, 2 interceptions. I think personally it's perfectly fair that Sterling is the man of the match here considering Aguero also missed an open goal.
